text.tspan: c. UKMTO Dubai4) Alter the tracking interval to “poll” vessels position every 15 minutes.5) Record of events to be maintained. Obtain following information about vessel: a) Date/Time of occurrence b) Position of vessel c) Any casualty or injury to personnel? d) Pirates’ demand?6) Notify Owners, charterers, Manning office, Flag Authority, Classification Society,7) H & M Underwriters and/or P & I Club if applicable.8) ‘Emergency Head Quarters’ at head office will be kept manned 24 X 7 for monitoring and response. CSO will liaise with all externalparties and communication may be directed through the designated numbers only.9) Establish close contact with: a) The IMB Piracy reporting Centre, in Kuala Lumpur. b) Other agencies, which may exert pressure for quick release of ship and c) seafarers. d) Provide all necessary assistance while seeking their help in resolving the situation.10) A team is designated in each concerned manning office to brief / update families on a daily basis.11) Arrange and make provision for: a) Negotiating with Pirates through a competent hostage negotiator appointed after b) consultation with P&I Club and Owners. c) Care of cargo in case it requires special needs (heating, inhibitors, etc.) d) Evacuation and repatriation of crew after release of vessel. e) Provision of Medical care as necessary. f) Psychological rehabilitation of seafarers, in case of prolonged detention.12) In consultation with Owners and chatterers arrange for their meeting with the Seafarers families to provide assurance.13) In consultation with the Owners appoint Media consultant.14) Media statement shall be prepared in consultation with Owners and issued by Managing director and also put up on the CompanyWebsite.15) All communication to be strictly controlled by CSO and regular briefings / updates to be issued, in consultation with head owners /negotiators.7.5.12POWER FAILURETo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of Power Failure, please refer to Section 4 ‘Emergency Procedures’ ofthe Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.2) To appoint a salvage company if considered necessary.3) Assess extent of damage to the generators/switchboard and seek expert advice from makers to try and get the power restored assoon as possible.4) If the vessel diverts or seeks port of refuge, general average to be declared.5) To assess cause of failure and arrange necessary spares and repairs at the first available opportunity.6) Arrange for superintendent to travel to attend the vessel if required.7) To ensure that the relevant form for power failure enclosed as appendix 12 has been filled in by the vessel.7.5.13SERIOUS INJURY/ CASUALTYTo confirm vessel`s compliance with actions required in case of Serious Injury / Casualty, please refer to Section 4 ‘EmergencyProcedures’ of the Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.2) Seek assistance from the nearest port authorities in order to provide medical assistance / evacuation as necessary.3) If necessary divert the vessel appoint agents and arrange for the crew member to be disembarked and treated.4) Notify next of kin.5) In case of fatality, consulate of the crew members country should be informed.7.5.14HEAVY WEATHER DAMAGE
